vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
    pad: 20
  }
}

title: |'md
# Archetype Concept: Memory Layout & Component Signatures
'| {near: top-center}

direction: right

# Archetype 1: Static Environment
archetype_1: "Archetype A: [Position]" {
  style: {
    fill: "#E8F4FD"
    stroke: "#2196F3"
    stroke-width: 2
    double-border: true
  }
  
  mem_layout_1: {
    shape: sql_table
    style.stroke: "#2196F3"
    header: "Memory Segment (Contiguous)"
    0x00: "Entity 0 | Pos(10.0, 20.0) | size: 8B" {constraint: f32_vec2}
    0x08: "Entity 3 | Pos(50.0, 80.0) | size: 8B" {constraint: f32_vec2}
    0x10: "Entity 7 | Pos(15.5, 35.2) | size: 8B" {constraint: f32_vec2}
    0x18: "Padding / Alignment | size: 8B" {style.fill: "#cfcfcf"}
  }
  
  note_1: |'md
**Signature: [Position]**
*Static environment objects*
- Memory Layout: `Struct{f32, f32}[N]`
- Linear Access / No Velocity
'| {
    shape: text
    style.font-size: 11
    style.font-color: "#333"
  }
}

# Archetype 2: Moving Projectiles
archetype_2: "Archetype B: [Position, Velocity]" {
  style: {
    fill: "#FFF3E0"
    stroke: "#FF9800"
    stroke-width: 2
    double-border: true
  }
  
  mem_layout_2: {
    shape: sql_table
    style.stroke: "#FF9800"
    header: "Memory Segment (SoA Layout)"
    0x00: "Entity 1 | Pos(10, 20) | Vel(5, 0)" {constraint: "16B"}
    0x10: "Entity 4 | Pos(30, 40) | Vel(-2, 3)" {constraint: "16B"}
    0x20: "Entity 8 | Pos(60, 70) | Vel(0, -1)" {constraint: "16B"}
    0x30: "Entity 9 | Pos(25, 55) | Vel(1, 1)" {constraint: "16B"}
  }
  
  note_2: |'md
**Signature: [Pos, Vel]**
*Moving projectiles / Non-living*
- Layout: Interleaved Component Arrays
- SIMD Friendly
'| {
    shape: text
    style.font-size: 11
    style.font-color: "#333"
  }
}

# Archetype 3: NPCs / Living Actors
archetype_3: "Archetype C: [Position, Velocity, Health]" {
  style: {
    fill: "#E8F5E9"
    stroke: "#4CAF50"
    stroke-width: 2
    double-border: true
  }
  
  mem_layout_3: {
    shape: sql_table
    style.stroke: "#4CAF50"
    header: "Memory Segment (Dense Actor Data)"
    0x00: "Ent 2 | P(10,20) | V(1,0) | HP: 100" {constraint: "20B"}
    0x14: "Ent 5 | P(30,40) | V(0,2) | HP: 75" {constraint: "20B"}
    0x28: "Ent 6 | P(50,60) | V(-1,1) | HP: 50" {constraint: "20B"}
  }
  
  note_3: |'md
**Signature: [Pos, Vel, HP]**
*Living Actors / NPCs*
- Dense data storage
- Frequent State Mutations
'| {
    shape: text
    style.font-size: 11
    style.font-color: "#333"
  }
}

# Documentation and insight block
insight: |'md
## Architectural Insight: Structural Grouping
Each Archetype functions as a unique table where every row has the **exact same** component set.

### Technical Advantages:
1. **Zero Indirection**: Components are adjacent in memory; no pointer chasing.
2. **SIMD Optimization**: Systems process Archetype B with SIMD (AVX/SSE) without branching.
3. **Query Filtering**: `Query<Pos, Vel>` identifies Archetype B and C, skipping A.
'| {
  near: bottom-right
  shape: text
  style: {
    fill: "#FAFAFA"
    stroke: "#9E9E9E"
    stroke-dash: 3
  }
}

# Logic Flow / Query Visualization
query_container: {
  style.stroke-width: 0
  style.fill: transparent
  
  query_label: "System Query: Needs (Position, Velocity)" {
    shape: rectangle
    style: {
      fill: "#FF9800"
      font-color: white
      bold: true
      border-radius: 999
    }
  }
}

# Connection showing matching logic
query_container.query_label -> archetype_2: "Exact Match" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#FF9800"
    stroke-width: 3
    stroke-dash: 5
    animated: true
  }
}

query_container.query_label -> archetype_3: "Superset Match" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4CAF50"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 5
    animated: true
  }
}

# Cross-archetype relationships
archetype_1 -- archetype_2: "Incompatible Layout" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#9E9E9E"
    stroke-dash: 3
    opacity: 0.4
  }
}

archetype_2 -- archetype_3: "Shared Component Offset" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#9E9E9E"
    stroke-dash: 3
    opacity: 0.4
  }
}